productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: If you are looking for a computer that is portable, eco-friendly, versatile, stylish and powerful, the Zotac ZBOX-ID86-BE mini-PC is what you seek. Mini-PCs are the next step in the evolution of personal computers and Zotac offers some of the finest mini-PCs around. The compact nature of the Zotac ZBOX-ID86-BE mini-PC allows it to blend right into any room, be it your home or office, without occupying too much space. Extremely light, you can effortlessly carry this mini-PC around and link it to any compatible display screen so as to turn the latter into a makeshift computer - its that easy! Performance The Zotac ZBOX-ID86-BE mini-PC is equipped with an Intel Atom D2550 processor (a dual-core processor that can hit a clock speed of 1.86 GHz) and an Intel NM10 chipset. This mini-PC offers a processor cache of 1 MB. Hence, all the tasks and processes assigned to this computer will be done in a jiffy. Capable of supporting DDR3 RAM of up to 4 GB, the Zotac ZBOX-ID86-BE mini-PC runs on the Windows operating system which makes system navigation a breeze. Furthermore, this mini-PC contains space for a 2.5-inch hard drive disk. Audiovisual Features Boasting a mighty NVIDIA GeForce GT 610 graphics processing unit, the Zotac ZBOX-ID86-BE is able to render impeccably detailed images on the compatible display screen that you have connected it to, hence, your favourite movies, TV shows or video games will come to life on your TV screen or monitor. In addition, the PureVideo HD technology coupled with the HDMI 1.4a feature further enhances the audiovisual capabilities of this mini-PC. Connectivity Convert any room into a media centre by attaching a slew of compatible external device into the USB 3.0 and USB 2.0 ports of the Zotac ZBOX-ID86-BE. Following this, based on your preferences and requisites, you can connect an external keyboard, mouse and any other compatible device to this mini-PC to fulfill your technological/entertainment-based needs.

productBaseInfoV1.title: Zotac ZBOX-ID18-E - Intel NM70 Express, Intel Processor, DDR3  Barebone Mini PC
productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: Are you looking for a highly portable and versatile computer that can deliver a powerful performance? Well, the Zotac ZBOX-ID18-E Mini PC is what you seek. Extremely light, this Mini-PC can be effortlessly carried around and all you need to do to utilize it is connect it to a compatible display screen such as a monitor or TV, be it in your house or your office. Energy efficient, the Zotac ZBOX-ID18-E requires very little power to function. Furthermore, you no longer have to be worried about burdening your room space with unnecessary computer-related equipment as this compact PC solves that problem. Performance Comprising of an Intel NM70 Express chipset, a processor cache of 2 MB and an Intel dual-core processor that can hit a clock speed of 1.5 GHz, the Zotac ZBOX-ID18-E can get numerous tasks and processes done in no time. This Mini-PC supports DDR3 RAM of up to 16 GB. You can also connect a 2.5-inch SATA HDD into the provided drive bay. The Zotac ZBOX-ID18-E functions on the Windows operating system, hence, navigating this computer is a breeze. Audiovisual Features Watching movies, TV shows and playing adrenaline-pumping video games have just become more enjoyable and magical as the Zotac ZBOX-ID18-E comes equipped with an Intel HD Graphics graphics processing unit that renders detailed images on the display screen that this Mini-PC is linked to. Furthermore, this Mini-PC delivers stereo sound and you can get an impressive 8-channel surround audio experience by connecting the necessary audio output devices to the provided HDMI port - create an immersive home theatre within the comfort of your house or any place you please. Connectivity Two USB 3.0 ports and four USB 2.0 ports have been built into this Mini-PC to which you can link an array of compatible devices like a keyboard, mouse and much more so as to accomplish all your computer-related needs. Furthermore, the Zotac ZBOX-ID18-E is also endowed with a 6-in-1 card reader. Usage Firstly, connect the provided adapter to your Zotac ZBOX-ID18-E to power it up. Following this, based on your preferences and requisites, you can connect an external keyboard, mouse and any other compatible device to this Mini-PC to fulfill your technological and entertainment-based needs.

productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: Looking for a handy, portable media centre? You have just found it. The Zotac ZBOX EI730 Mini-PC is a marvel of modern-day technological ingenuity. Compact, this Mini-PC can be carried around with very little effort and it can be connected to any compatible display screen so as to be used. Energy-conscious, the Zotac ZBOX EI730 requires very little power to work. Don’t let the tiny size of this computer fool you; it is capable of giving you a truly powerful performance. Furthermore, this Mini-PC doesn’t clutter up the room that you are using it in unlike many other computers and their accessories. Performance Equipped with an Intel Core i5 4570R quad-core processor that can hit a clock speed of 2.7 GHz, the Zotac ZBOX EI730 is able to give you a truly remarkable computing experience as it can execute multiple tasks and processes in the snap of a finger. This Mini-PC runs on the Windows operating system which makes system navigation a breeze. A DDR3 RAM of up to 16 GB is accommodated by this Mini-PC. A 2.5-inch drive bay has been built into this computer so that you can install a SATA HDD and have the memory to store all you favourite digital content. Audiovisual Features Prepare yourself to have a truly spellbinding gaming experience as the Zotac ZBOX EI730 comes with the new Intel Iris Pro 5200 graphics processing unit and the Intel Collage Display Technology which dramatically enhance picture quality and make images very crisp and crystal clear. In addition, movies and TV shows will come to life in the room that you watch them in thanks to the aforementioned features. When it comes to the audio capabilities of the Zotac ZBOX EI730, it can deliver a stereo sound and a majestic 8-channel surround audio system can be configured by connecting the necessary audio output equipment to this Mini-PC via the HDMI interface - what better way to watch a high-octane action film than on a home theatre? Connectivity Four USB 3.0 ports have been included in the Zotac ZBOX EI730, hence, you can connect the compatible external devices that you prefer, such as, a keyboard, mouse and more. productBaseInfoV1.title: Zotac ZBOX-ID88 - Intel H61 Express, Intel Core i3 3220T, DDR3  Barebone Mini PC
productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: Technological convenience has been redefined now that Zotac has come out with the ZBOX-ID88 Mini PC. Here are a few vital characteristics you need to know about this Mini-PC: it’s portable - you can carry around this tiny featherweight of a PC effortlessly; it’s energy efficient and it's compatible with Windows 7 and 8. You can carry around this Mini-PC and connect it to any compatible display screen to convert the latter into a monitor. Performance Built with an Intel H61 Express chipset and an Intel Core i3 3220T dual-core processor (delivers a clock speed of 2.8 GHz) that is integrated with Intel Hyper-Threading Technology, the ZBOX-ID88 allows you to perform numerous tasks and processes at the same time in an effortless manner. Also, this Mini-PC offers a 3 MB processor cache which further contributes to its performance. The Windows operating system allows for a seamless system navigation. The ZBOX-ID88 supports DDR3 RAM of up to 16 GB. Furthermore, this Mini-PC can accommodate a 2.5-inch SATA HDD or SSD. Audiovisual Features Equipped with an integrated Intel HD Graphics 2500 graphics processing unit, the ZBOX-ID88 allows you to watch movies and TV shows in impressive clarity. You can also play many adrenaline-pumping games that require a good graphics card to back them up. In addition, on the audio front, the ZBOX-ID88 can support an 8-channel audio surround system, hence, you can create a home theatre wherever you please if you have the necessary audio equipment to complement this Mini-PC. A headphone/microphone jack is another sound-related feature that has been included in the ZBOX-ID88. Connectivity The Dual Gigabit LAN feature ensures that two discrete intranet/internet connections can be established. Stronger Bluetooth/Wi-Fi reception is certain as 2 external antennas are a part of this Mini-PC. Various compatible external devices like a keyboard, mouse and more can be connected to the two USB 3.0 ports or two USB 2.0 ports that have been built into the ZBOX-ID88. A HDMI 1.4a audio/video interface and a 4-in-1 memory card are other noteworthy adds. Usage: Firstly, connect the provided adapter to your ZBOX-ID88 to power it up. Following this, based on your preferences and requisites, you can connect an external keyboard, mouse and any other compatible device to this Mini-PC to fulfill your technological and entertainment-based needs.

productBaseInfoV1.productDescription: Experience the future of technological ingenuity with the Zotac ZBOXNANO-ID63 Mini PC. Portable, energy-conscious, versatile and capable of giving a powerful performance, this Mini-PC can be carried around effortlessly on the face of your palm and connected to any compatible display screen so as to make the latter a temporary/permanent computer. Furthermore, this Mini-PC also utilizes very little energy. Performance The Zotac ZBOXNANO-ID63 is endowed with an Intel HM77 Express and the third generation of Intel Core processors (Intel Core i3 3227U dual-core processor) that can deliver a clock speed of 1.9 GHz. All the tasks and processes that are assigned to this computer will be executed in a jiffy - no more wasting time when it comes to your computer-related work or entertainment-based pursuits. This Mini-PC supports DDR3 RAM of up to 8 GB. A 2.5-inch drive bay has been included in this Mini-PC which can accommodate a SATA HDD or SSD. Functioning on the Windows operating system, you can navigate this Mini-PC with great ease. Audiovisual Features Watching your favourite movies, TV shows or playing high-octane games will never be the same as this Mini-PC comes equipped with the Intel HD Graphics 4000 graphics processing unit. This graphics card makes all the images that are rendered on the display screen of your computer crisp and crystal clear. While the Intel Quick Sync technology makes video conversion lightning-fast, the Intel Clear Video HD technology further enhances the picture quality. When it comes to the aural features of this Mini-PC, The Zotac ZBOXNANO-ID63 comes with a headphone/microphone jack and you can also derive 8-channel surround audio via the HDMI that has been provided in this product - make an immersive home theatre within the comfort of your home. Connectivity Wireless network connectivity enabled, this Mini-PC comes with four USB 3.0 ports and two USB 2.0 ports which open up an array of possibilities with regard to connectivity. You can link an external keyboard, mouse and many other compatible devices to this Zotac ZBOXNANO-AQ01 so as to realize its full potential. A 7-in-1 card reader is another noteworthy add. Usage Firstly, connect the provided adapter to the Zotac ZBOXNANO-AQ01 to power it up. Following this, based on your preferences and requisites, you can connect an external keyboard, mouse and any other compatible device to this Mini-PC to fulfill your technological and entertainment-based needs.

Due to Windows 32-bit operating system limitation, when more than 4 GB of physical memory is installed, the actual memory size displayed will be less than 4 GB. The DVI-D port does not support D-Sub connection by adapter. Simultaneous output for DVI-D and the MDP2 Thunderbolt port is not supported. When a monitor connected to the DVI-D port, the MDP2 Thunderbolt port can support Thunderbolt storage device(s) only. Due to PC architecture I/O resources limitation, the amount of the Thunderbolt devices can be used is dependent on the quantity of PCI Express and PCI devices be installed. For optimum performance, if only one PCI Express graphics card is to be installed, be sure to install it in the PCIEX16 slot. The PCIEX8 slot shares bandwidth with the PCIEX16 slot. When the PCIEX8 slot is populated, the PCIEX16 slot will operate at up to x8 mode. The PCIEX4 slot is available only when an Intel 22 nm (Ivy Bridge) CPU is installed. The PCIEX4 slot shares bandwidth with the PCIEX8 and PCIEX16 slots. When the PCIEX4 slot is populated, the PCIEX16 slot will operate at up to x8 mode and the PCIEX8 will operate at up to x4 mode. Whether PCI Express 3.0 is supported depends on CPU and graphics card ompatibility. The SATA2 5 connector will become unavailable when the mSATA connector is installed with a solid state drive. When a RAID set is built across the SATA 6 Gb/s and SATA 3 Gb/s channels, the system performance of the RAID set may vary depending on the devices being connected. In Windows XP, the Intel USB 3.0 ports can support up to USB 2.0 transfer speed. Due to a Windows 7 limitation, please connect your USB device(s) to the USB 2.0/1.1 port(s) before the VIA USB 3.0 controller driver is installed.
